2. promote the rational use of natural resources so as to safeguard and protect the bio-diversity of Uganda.

1. The foreign policy of Uganda shall be based on the principles of-
promotion of the national interest of Uganda;


International law
respect for international law and treaty obligations;
peaceful co-existence and non-alignment;
settlement of international disputes by peaceful means;
opposition to all forms of domination, racism and other forms of oppression and exploitation.
2. promotion of the national interest of Uganda;
3. 

International law
respect for international law and treaty obligations;
4. peaceful co-existence and non-alignment;
5. settlement of international disputes by peaceful means;
6. opposition to all forms of domination, racism and other forms of oppression and exploitation.
7. 

International organizations
Uganda shall actively participate in international and regional organisations that stand for peace and for the well-being and progress of humanity.
8. 

Regional group(s)
The State shall promote regional and pan-African cultural, economic and political cooperation and integration.
1. promotion of the national interest of Uganda;
