1. A regional assembly may establish standing and other committees or organs for the efficient discharge of its functions.
2. The representatives of cultural interests shall constitute the standing committee on cultural matters.
3. The standing committee on cultural matters shall have, as against the rest of the members of the regional assembly, exclusive jurisdiction on the cultural matters of the region.
4. In this paragraph "cultural matters" include the following-
the choice and installation of a traditional leader or cultural leader;
all traditional and cultural matters relating to the traditional or cultural leader and to the institutions of the traditional leader or cultural leader as well as royal members of the traditional leadership;
the choice, appointment and succession to clan and sub-clan leadership;
clan, traditional and customary matters;
matters relating to cultural funeral rites, cultural succession and customary heirs;
cultural or traditional lands, sites, shrines and installations;
clan lands, sites, shrines and installation; and
traditional, customary and cultural practices which are consistent with this Constitution.
