The functions and services for which a regional government is responsible are as follows-
1. secondary education and tertiary institutions except national universities and other national institutions;
2. regional roads;
3. regional referral hospitals other than national referral hospitals and national medical institutions;
4. co-ordination, monitoring and supervision of agriculture;
5. forests, other than, forests, national parks and wildlife reserves managed by the Government;
6. culture;
7. cultural and traditional lands;
8. 

Protection of language use
promotion of local languages, crafts and antiquities;
9. water;
10. sanitation;
11. to levy surcharge or cess subject to the approval of Central Government;
12. functions and services surrendered voluntarily by a district council or district councils;
13. receiving copies of financial accountability of districts to the Central Government to enable the regional government monitor and supervise the implementation of government programmes.

